[b]Time-to-React + Volatility Time[/b] measures how quickly and cleanly price reacts after key market structure events — Break of Structure, liquidity sweeps, and Order Block taps — and scores that reaction relative to the current volatility environment.

[b]What it does[/b]

After a structure event fires, the indicator tracks the subsequent bars and scores how fast price moves, how cleanly it validates the event, and whether the move is proportional to prevailing volatility. A separate volatility activity score contextualizes the reaction score. The combination surfaces whether a structure event produced a convincing, timely follow-through — or a sluggish, low-quality reaction.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Event tracking[/b] — Scores reactions after BOS, liquidity sweep, and Order Block events
[*][b]Reaction score[/b] — Measures speed and validation quality of the post-event move
[*][b]Volatility activity score[/b] — Independent measure of current market activity, used to contextualize reaction quality
[*][b]Timeframe presets[/b] — Auto-selects parameter sets by timeframe with optional manual overrides
[*][b]Display options[/b] — Panel view with optional chart labels and candle coloring
[/list]

